    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT372-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">iravukkuṟi vantoḻukāniṉṟa talaimakaṉ kēṭpat tōḻi talaimakaṭkuc
                    colluvāḷāyc colliyatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by the confidante, as one who speaks to
                    HER, for HIM to hear, who stood there motionless, having come to the night
                    tryst. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT372">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> paṉaittalaik karukkuṭai neṭumaṭal kuruttoṭu māyak</l>
                    <l> kaṭuvaḷi tokutta neṭuveṇ kuppaik</l>
                    <l> kaṇaṅkoḷ cimaiya vaṇaṅkuṅ kāṉa</l>
                    <l> lāḻitalai vīciya vayirccēṟ ṟaruvik</l>
                    <l> kūḻaipe yekkark kuḻīiya patukkai</l>
                    <l> pularpataṅ koḷḷā vaḷavai</l>
                    <l> yalareḻun taṉṟiv vaḻunka lūrē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l rend="indent"> Before the mounds accumulated in the dunes</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> reached dry consistency, to be poured on the hair ,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> from the river mouth with mud [and] fine sand flung</l>
                    <l rend="indent9"> by the sea’s [wave] heads ,</l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> in the seashore grove, where the peaks in groups are yielding </l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> to the long white heaps piled up by the fierce wind,</l>
                    <l rend="indent4"> so that with the sprouts the saw-edged long stems</l>
                    <l rend="indent6"> disappear up to the top of the Palmyras, </l>
                    <l> gossip arose in this noisy village.</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
